        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Herman Singer (1915-2001) was an editor of the 
                <emph render="italic">New Leader</emph> from 1945-1950. He worked for Radio Free Europe (RFE) and was active in their alumni organization, the Society of International Broadcasters. He edited the publication 
                <emph render="italic">East Europe</emph> in the 1960s and 1970s wrote on V. F. Calverton, proletarian literature and Socialist Party history, and reviewed books and films.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This collection contains correspondence and documents relating to his work on Calverton, Socialist Party history, NY Call/SDF, the Newspaper Guild-Free Europe Unit, and 
                <emph render="italic">Free Europe Guild News</emph>. Also included is correspondence with Bob Rindel, Sam Solon, Calverton and various editors and publishers. PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
        </scopecontent>
